Reasoning: The paper deals with reconfiguration variants of two classical vertex-subset problems, namely Independent Set and Dominating Set, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and combinatorics. The paper also discusses the complexity of these problems on graphs of bounded bandwidth, degeneracy, treewidth, and nowhere-dense graphs, which are important concepts in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
